<p><alert>Solution</alert>: Dividing both sides of the equation by 144, we get:</p>
<p><image source="/media/png72/imageC2316.png" /> or <image source="/media/png72/imageC2317.png" />.</p>
<p>This is equation of a vertical ellipse at standard position with <em>a=</em>4, so vertices at (0, ±4), and</p>
